Baseline Reproduction Summary

What was reproduced
- Reproduced the baseline described in the research paper text in docs/research-pdf-text using the UCI Wine Quality dataset.
- Implemented the same model set: Decision Tree, Random Forest, SVM, KNN, and Gradient Boosting (XGBoost).

Data preparation and setup
- Quality was converted to 3 classes: low (<=4), medium (5-6), high (>=7).
- Features were standardized using z-score scaling.
- Train/test split used 70/30 with stratification.
- SMOTE was applied to the training set to address class imbalance.

Model training and evaluation
- Hyperparameters were tuned with Optuna and the best parameters were used for the reproduction run.
- Metrics computed: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, and ROC-AUC (multi-class OVR).

Baseline comparison to the paper
- The script prints Accuracy, F1-Score, and ROC-AUC for each model and compares them to the paper results.
- Each metric is flagged as OK if the difference from the paper is within +/- 0.05 to account for minor library and sampling differences.

